The intro to “Ride On” from The Fantastic Machine album…

Recorded at @hydestreetstudios in #sanfrancisco 

#femaleguitarist #guitar #california #gibson #pamelaparker #thefantasticmachine #singersongwriter #songwriter

I really enjoyed doing the @working_class_audio podcast with @matt_boudreau talking about my life & journey as an audio engineer & music producer. I currently work out of the SF Bay Area at @hydestreetstudios (my musical home away from home:-)

I often look at my life and feel so lucky to be doing what I love! Regularly working with so many talented artists in the process. It’s one of my passions in life to meet new people and share music! 

Producing music has always been one of the main ways I love sharing my own and others’ music in this lifetime! One of my favorite things is that recordings will last beyond this lifetime. 
It’s one of the ways our spirits live forever on Earth. 

Loved ❤️💜❤️ talking shop with Matt and reminiscing about the recording studio journey I’ve been on that lead me to where I am now! There have been so many studios, artists, emotions and a range of experiences along the way. Would never change a thing!

Check out the link in my bio or you can go to www.workingclassaudio.com or even search “Working Class Audio” on platforms @spotify @google @applemusic and you’ll find me under Episode #417

...in just 7 Days 22 Hours 55 Mins & 55 Secs the gates to High Sierra Music Festival...and ya’ll know that Pamela Parker’s Fantastic Machine will be playing a set at High Sierra Music Festival this year!!!

After many years of contributing to Guitarmageddon and doing the kids workshops, I’ll be music directing the playshop “Rock The Funk Out!!!” on Sunday, July 2nd from 1:45 - 2:45PM in the High Sierra Music Hall.

Rock The Funk Out!!! will feature PPFM with JaeStix on Drums, Steven La Bella on Bass, Chris Hoog on Sax, Amber “Funky Fitzy” Fitzgerald on vocals, Jordan Feinstein on keys and we will be having some super extra special guests like Benjamin Andrews on guitar, Brenden Lui on trumpet, Ben Misterka on guitar, Dave Combs on vocals, Tony Hall of Dumpstaphunk, and more guests from Diggin Dirt, Boot Juice and Jaimeson Durr coming in to mix our set!

Thank you forever and big ups to Sean Leahy for always being like a brother to me and involving me in this fun festival over the years! I feel blessed to be a part of Guitarmageddon for so many years and being my Bay Area family, love you guys more than you know!!!!

This year Benjamin Andrews will be music directing Guitarmageddon and Con Brio will be the backing band...ya’ll know what that means it’s gonna be...of the chizZzainn!!!

Along with all of that, I’ll also be hosting the morning interactive playshops where you can come jam with us on stage (and you can jam along off stage too)...check out Friday, Saturday & Sunday mornings from 10-11am in the High Sierra Music Hall. Themes are Friday - Blues, Saturday - Rock, & Sunday - Funk.

We will be rockin’ it all weekend long...see you there!!!

Come one, come all to the best party of the summer... High Sierra Music Festival...get ur tickets now!

See you there!!!

@chinadollsmusic did an #artistspotlight on me for our upcoming shows at @ashkenazberkeley (#saturday ) and at @crazylikeahorse (#friday #tonight ) with @sunbecker , Jen Rund, @richellecali , @jbottari & @annaelvadrums for some fun playing @gratefuldead for a couple nights! 

Come out and hang with us!!! 

Here’s what I said: 
“I feel so blessed to call these China Dolls all my sisters, and this kind of a thing happens in the Bay Area music scene!  Real people coming together for a common bond to share music we all love with people who also love it! There's a circular motion to playing music for people who are really listening and really into it...they give back so much energy of their own by dancing, singing along, etc.  It's that we are together, all of us at one venue, the energy grows so big and is so beautiful!  This is one of my favorite things about playing live, sharing the love!  I cannot wait to see everyone out there at the shows this coming weekend. 

In the Bay Area, I'm extremely grateful to continue working as a Music Producer & Audio Engineer at the historic landmark recording studio, Hyde Street Studios in San Francisco.  This place is especially important to me now, because the China Dolls are going to be playing some of the tunes the Grateful Dead wrote and recorded at Hyde Street Studios back in the day.  I mean, there is some real history in those walls.  The Grateful Dead and their friends aka Janis Joplin & Jefferson Airplane (just to name a few of the regulars), all hung out there and wrote songs and recorded on their off time from performing.  This is what my friends and I do now at Hyde Street Studios.  One of my current visions for China Dolls is to bring them to Hyde Street Studios after a few tours and then record a bunch of the songs the GD wrote and recorded there many years ago.  And then finally, write some new tunes to put out into the world.  The next generation of Grateful Dead...the vibe would just be so right!

See everyone out there this weekend...”
